Our education sector would be brought to an abrupt shutdown, thanks to its reliance on the brick-and-mortar in-person mode of delivery. First came the hospitality industry, as flights got grounded.Children got to see the faces of their parents, mostly fathers, after a long while. Like any other new year, 2020 began with lots of optimism and great promise. I remember folks joking about it, pronouncing it as ‘dwendy dwendy’ idiosyncratic of some native dialectic.
It was billed as a year of double blessings as indicated by the ‘double twenty’. Then Covid-19 happened. The events that would later unfold were like a huge mirror placed before us, reflecting our real situation; our real strengths and vulnerabilities.



