At individual levels, we equally learned lessons. Parents learned the importance of teachers, seeing how children had outwitted them in their own homes. Various individuals would be forced to spend long hours with close family members, with some getting into friction with one another.
Children got to see the faces of their parents, mostly fathers, after a long while. Chicken had finally come home to roost.
Against all this, we reckoned the magnitude of work ahead of us. There are debts to be paid, relationships to be repaired, firms to be revived, and so many other broken pieces that need to be reassembled.
Whereas many lives and livelihoods were regrettably lost, the fact that we are still alive provides reassurance that we are conquerors — whether by divine power or sheer resilience. We therefore have another chance to breathe new life into our struggles, and make our existence more meaningful not only to ourselves but to humanity in general. Lessons learnt should guide us into the New Year and subsequent futures.





